[div class=p 
	[em 
		"If you bounce long enough into the void, the void begins to bounce back through you.
	]em
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a href=https://libra-bits.itch.io/super-hard-bouncer-gameboy-game rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Super Hard Bouncer
	]a
	" is a simple yet hard platformer homebrew for Game Boy developed by 
	[a href=https://twitter.com/libra_bits rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Libra Bits
	]a
	". In 20 quick levels, you have to bounce, avoid spikes and enemies, grab powerups, and avoid the void.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The bouncing is automatic, you can control the bounce height (0x18 pixels) by either holding the down button(0x6 pixels) or pressing the A button before the jump (0x1B pixels).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There's walljump! If you manage to reach a wall as close as 0x10 subpixels from its surface, if you're ascending you bonk downwards, but if you're descending you get a walljump. This is abused in several levels, not only to move faster but also to break levels entirely.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In version 1.0, there was a game breaking oversight: you could enter the screen lateral void and warp to other side of the level. I was making a TAS of this version but the developer updated the game to 1.1 fixing this error. You can see a complete run abusing this error 
	[a href=https://youtu.be/XJSoooCOiqc rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"here
	]a
	". After I finished the 1.0 TAS, I ported it to 1.1, re-doing the levels I broke with this glitch, adjusting desync issue with subpixels being preserved during level transitions, and gladly finding a few faster strats in some levels.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Feel free to use 
	[a href=https://github.com/brunovalads/tas-scripts/blob/master/Super%20Hard%20Bouncer/Super%20Hard%20Bouncer%20Script.lua rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"my lua script
	]a
	" and beat time.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"And if you know another bouncing ball game, please let me know, 
	[b 
		"I feed on them
	]b
	".
	$LF
]div
